verbs.description: unking (third-person singular simple present unkings, present participle unkinging, simple past and past participle unkinged)

examples: Synonyms: depose, dethrone, discrown, disenthrone, uncrown, unthrone

entries.meaning: (archaic) To deprive (a king) of his royal qualities.
examples: My swelling rage, in privacy I’le shrowd,
And not un-King my self before the Crowd.

entries.meaning: (archaic, figuratively) To remove (something) from a position of power or paramount importance.
examples: there was within me fresh Rebellion,
and reason was almost unking’d agen.
